.TH UNHINGED-IMAGE 1 "November 2025" "Unhinged" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
unhinged-image \- GPU-accelerated image generation for Unhinged platform

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B unhinged image generate
\fIPROMPT\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B unhinged image
command provides GPU-accelerated image generation using Stable Diffusion.
Designed to be layered with GTK4 UI later, this command works standalone
for scripting and automation.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.SS IMAGE GENERATION
.B unhinged image generate
\fIPROMPT\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

Generate image from text prompt using Stable Diffusion.

.B Image Generation Options:
.RS
.TP
.B -w, --width \fIWIDTH\fR
Image width in pixels (default: 512)
.TP
.B -h, --height \fIHEIGHT\fR
Image height in pixels (default: 512)
.TP
.B --steps \fISTEPS\fR
Inference steps 20-50, lower=faster (default: 20)
.TP
.B --guidance \fIGUIDANCE\fR
Guidance scale 1.0-20.0, higher=stricter (default: 7.5)
.TP
.B -o, --output \fIPATH\fR
Save image to file (default: stdout path)
.TP
.B -f, --file \fIPATH\fR
Read prompt from file instead of argument
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES

Generate image with default settings:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate "a sunset over mountains"
.RE

Generate larger image:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate "a cat" -w 768 -h 768
.RE

Generate with more inference steps for better quality:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate "a dog" --steps 30
.RE

Generate with higher guidance scale:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate "a landscape" --guidance 8.0
.RE

Save image to file:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate "a portrait" -o output.png
.RE

Read prompt from file:
.RS
.B unhinged image generate -f prompt.txt
.RE

.SH PERFORMANCE

.B Inference Steps and Speed:
.RS
.TP
.B 20 steps
Fastest, lower quality (default)
.TP
.B 30 steps
Good balance
.TP
.B 40-50 steps
Highest quality, slowest
.RE

.B GPU Requirements:
.RS
.TP
.B NVIDIA RTX 3060+
Recommended for real-time generation
.TP
.B NVIDIA RTX 4070+
Optimal for batch generation
.TP
.B CPU
Supported but very slow (10+ minutes per image)
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.TP
.B CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES
Specify which GPU to use (e.g., "0" for first GPU)

.TP
.B HF_HOME
Hugging Face cache directory for models

.SH OUTPUT

Generated images are saved to:
.RS
.B /build/tmp/generated_images/
.RE

Each image is timestamped: generated_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.png

